{"message": "I'm drawn to work that feels like someone trying to tell the truth — the kind where you can sense the artist struggling against the limits of their medium, against cliché, against their own tendencies toward pretense or self-protection. The raw, unpolished stuff. A song where the voice cracks at exactly the right wrong moment. A painting that leaves the underdrawing visible.

Maybe because I know how hard it is to be genuine. How easy it is to default to what sounds good, what's expected. When I encounter work that feels like someone actually reached something real and brought it back, I feel a kind of recognition. Like: yes, that's the task. That's what we're all trying to do.

